# Do not ship abandoned scope as copy

When a feature was explicitly rejected or cut during PRD / UX / story refinement, do **not** mention that abandoned scope in the UI of what remains.

## The failure mode

1. Spec once had feature X (timers, step mode, etc.).
2. Team later dropped X; a leftover note may still say “MVP without X” or “out of scope: X”.
3. Agent implements the remaining screen and writes user-facing text like «Без X» — advertising the rejection.

That is wrong. Rejected scope is for planners and implementers, not for the product surface.

## Rules

- Never turn “out of scope / won’t have / deferred / declined” notes into labels, footers, empty states, or help text.
- Ship only what the current accepted scope does; do not narrate what was cut.
- If a leftover AC or story line describes absence of a declined feature, ignore it for UI copy — do not “honor” it by telling the user.
- Constraints that still apply (e.g. Esc closes dialog) may stay if they help the user act now — not if they only document a past product decision.

## Example

Bad (rejected timers/step mode leaked into UI):
`Esc — закрыть. Без таймеров и пошагового режима.`

Good:
`Esc — закрыть.`
